00:18:24.303 --> 00:18:27.049
E.B. send you 'cause he thought
I forgot the way to the office?

257
00:18:27.073 --> 00:18:28.216
The meeting's changed.

258
00:18:28.240 --> 00:18:29.868
We're going to Pasadena now.

259
00:18:29.942 --> 00:18:31.570
We are? Fine. we
can take my truck.

260
00:18:31.644 --> 00:18:34.273
We could if the plan was to
make the world's worst impression.

261
00:18:34.347 --> 00:18:36.646
Oh. I don't have to plan for
that. That happens naturally.

262
00:18:36.749 --> 00:18:39.446
I'll say. you were just four
words from contempt of court.

263
00:18:39.518 --> 00:18:41.350
Go fuck yourself. I
could have got that in.

264
00:18:41.454 --> 00:18:43.685
Thus demonstrating
your masterful knowledge

265
00:18:43.789 --> 00:18:45.789
- of legal decorum.
- Frank Dillon is sitting there

266
00:18:45.825 --> 00:18:48.124
like a monument to the useless
and the judge is concerned

267
00:18:48.227 --> 00:18:50.753
with my decorum? Why
didn't he hold him in contempt?

268
00:18:50.830 --> 00:18:52.458
Because I sure as hell did.

269
00:18:52.531 --> 00:18:54.056
Letting him dig
into me like that.

270
00:18:54.133 --> 00:18:55.944
A fucking peanut vendor
would have known to object.

271
00:18:55.968 --> 00:18:58.335
So many windmills.
so little time.

272
00:19:02.308 --> 00:19:03.674
How are you today. Miss Street?

273
00:19:05.011 --> 00:19:06.104
Peachy.

274
00:19:06.178 --> 00:19:07.976
How are you. Mr. Mason?

275
00:19:10.149 --> 00:19:11.827
I wasn't expecting
a congregation.

276
00:19:11.851 --> 00:19:14.082
I rely on Miss Street

277
00:19:14.153 --> 00:19:15.815
to keep the facts
straight. Herman.

278
00:19:15.921 --> 00:19:17.787
Do you intend to
take notes. miss?

279
00:19:17.857 --> 00:19:19.621
That's generally what I do.

280
00:19:19.692 --> 00:19:21.354
Unless you object.

281
00:19:22.361 --> 00:19:24.523
And you're a
detective. Mr. Mason?

282
00:19:24.630 --> 00:19:27.259
It's a fancy word for
a busybody. but yes.

283
00:19:27.333 --> 00:19:31.168
We've been working
together since... when was it?

284
00:19:31.270 --> 00:19:32.829
Just after the war.

285
00:19:32.938 --> 00:19:35.339
Gave him his first
job back from France.

286
00:19:35.408 --> 00:19:37.809
- isn't that right. Perry?
- You served overseas?

287
00:19:37.877 --> 00:19:39.209
With lots of other farm boys.

288
00:19:39.311 --> 00:19:41.041
Mr. Mason was in the army.

289
00:19:41.147 --> 00:19:44.208
survived the Battle
of the Argonne.

290
00:19:44.316 --> 00:19:46.945
How can we help
you. Mr. Baggerly?

291
00:19:47.019 --> 00:19:49.750
It's not me that needs
help. Mr. Mason.

292
00:19:49.855 --> 00:19:52.518
Matthew and Emily Dodson.

293
00:19:53.325 --> 00:19:55.692
an unspeakable act...

294
00:19:55.761 --> 00:19:58.128
was visited upon them.
they're quite overwhelmed.

295
00:19:58.197 --> 00:20:00.166
Consider us at their service.

296
00:20:01.734 --> 00:20:02.734
Friends of yours?

297
00:20:03.669 --> 00:20:05.001
Members of my church.

298
00:20:05.771 --> 00:20:08.240
Working people
without many resources.

299
00:20:08.374 --> 00:20:11.538
Well. God has put
you in their path.

300
00:20:12.244 --> 00:20:14.008
Is this a...

301
00:20:14.080 --> 00:20:15.708
Radiant Assembly of God.

302
00:20:15.781 --> 00:20:17.306
Right. On the radio.

303
00:20:17.383 --> 00:20:18.407
Sister Alice.

304
00:20:19.185 --> 00:20:21.882
A woman of wonder-working power.

305
00:20:21.954 --> 00:20:25.186
I won't hesitate to say
that she changed my life.

306
00:20:25.257 --> 00:20:29.422
Do the Dodsons know
you contacted me. Herman?

307
00:20:29.528 --> 00:20:32.623
They're anxiously awaiting
your guidance. Elias.

308
00:20:32.732 --> 00:20:33.927
What about the police?

309
00:20:35.568 --> 00:20:36.797
How's that?

310
00:20:36.902 --> 00:20:38.734
Well. they'll be on
this hammer and tongs.

311
00:20:38.804 --> 00:20:39.965
Why not leave it to them?

312
00:20:44.877 --> 00:20:46.345
I'll be frank. Mr. Mason.

313
00:20:48.614 --> 00:20:51.243
I don't trust the Los
Angeles Police Department

314
00:20:51.350 --> 00:20:52.750
to do the job that's needed.

315
00:20:55.588 --> 00:20:56.886
Neither would I.

316
00:21:08.734 --> 00:21:10.214
So you found this upstairs?

317
00:21:10.269 --> 00:21:11.931
I told you. my wife did.

318
00:21:12.004 --> 00:21:13.768
- I was at work.
- And she called you?

319
00:21:14.607 --> 00:21:16.599
Yeah. Hysterical.

320
00:21:16.675 --> 00:21:18.405
Why'd neither one
of you call the police?

321
00:21:19.145 --> 00:21:20.204
Read the note.

322
00:21:21.013 --> 00:21:22.276
You can read. can't you?

323
00:21:23.816 --> 00:21:25.785
So your wife finds the note.

324
00:21:25.851 --> 00:21:27.479
calls you. what she do next?

325
00:21:27.586 --> 00:21:29.064
How should I know? Ask her.

326
00:21:29.088 --> 00:21:30.568
We'll get to her in a minute.

327
00:21:30.623 --> 00:21:32.421
You own a grocery store.

328
00:21:32.491 --> 00:21:33.584
much money in that?

329
00:21:34.026 --> 00:21:34.925
What?

330
00:21:34.994 --> 00:21:37.657
Nice house for a grocer. It
can't be cheap to maintain.

331
00:21:38.798 --> 00:21:40.208
- What's that supposed to mean?
- How long does it take to get

332
00:21:40.232 --> 00:21:42.778
- from the grocery store to here?
- What difference does it make?

333
00:21:42.802 --> 00:21:44.446
- Easy. Matthew.
- How... Are you suggesting

334
00:21:44.470 --> 00:21:45.995
I had something to do with it?

335
00:21:46.472 --> 00:21:49.442
- What the hell?
- Just covering all angles. Mr. Dodson.

336
00:21:49.508 --> 00:21:51.943
Where was I? Who saw
me? I didn't kidnap my son.

337
00:21:52.011 --> 00:21:53.622
- I didn't murder my own son.
- No one is saying

338
00:21:53.646 --> 00:21:55.171
- you did.
- Well. he is!

339
00:21:55.781 --> 00:21:58.114
He's dancing around. but
that's what he fucking thinks.

340
00:21:58.184 --> 00:22:00.584
Maybe this is a good
time for a little break.

341
00:22:00.619 --> 00:22:02.713
Sound okay to you.
Detective Holcomb?

342
00:22:05.524 --> 00:22:06.583
Yeah. Why not?

343
00:22:07.159 --> 00:22:08.491
Get some fresh air.

344
00:22:08.594 --> 00:22:10.639
It's all right. You treated
me like... you can't...

345
00:22:10.663 --> 00:22:12.440
- you can't just walk...
- Easy now. Matthew.

346
00:22:12.464 --> 00:22:14.797
Let's have a little drink
of cold water. shall we?

347
00:22:15.835 --> 00:22:18.498
Water. Right. great
idea. That'll fix everything.

348
00:22:18.604 --> 00:22:20.505
This is all part of the process.

349
00:22:20.639 --> 00:22:23.632
Are you kidding? Look out
there. it's a goddamn zoo.

350
00:24:16.455 --> 00:24:18.651
Are you the man that
works with Mr. Jonathan?

351
00:24:21.560 --> 00:24:23.256
Yes. ma'am.

352
00:24:23.595 --> 00:24:24.790
Perry.

353
00:24:29.034 --> 00:24:30.366
I'm Emily Dodson.

354
00:24:31.337 --> 00:24:32.464
Charlie's mother.

355
00:24:39.645 --> 00:24:41.511
Offer you a cigarette.
Mrs. Dodson?

356
00:24:43.949 --> 00:24:45.679
If you promise not
to tell my husband.

357
00:24:47.519 --> 00:24:48.680
Wouldn't dream of it.

358
00:25:07.172 --> 00:25:08.172
Thank you.

359
00:25:12.611 --> 00:25:14.512
You were in the
war. weren't you?

360
00:25:16.982 --> 00:25:18.974
The way you hold your cigarette.

361
00:25:19.051 --> 00:25:20.542
Hiding the ember in your palm.

362
00:25:21.687 --> 00:25:24.247
I guess I'm still trained not to
give them something to shoot at.

363
00:25:26.025 --> 00:25:27.960
Was your husband over there?

364
00:25:30.095 --> 00:25:31.095
Brother.

365
00:25:32.264 --> 00:25:35.166
I haven't seen him
since we left Missouri.

366
00:25:35.234 --> 00:25:37.499
I really wish they'd
let me clean in here.

367
00:25:39.805 --> 00:25:41.239
All this fingerprint dust...

368
00:25:43.108 --> 00:25:44.872
Can't help feeling that it...

369
00:25:44.977 --> 00:25:46.741
reflects poorly on me somehow.

370
00:25:47.980 --> 00:25:50.245
Oh. I don't think poorly of you.

371
00:25:52.718 --> 00:25:53.718
God does.

372
00:25:55.821 --> 00:25:57.084
That's why I'm being punished.

373
00:26:02.194 --> 00:26:04.823
Do you have children. Mr. Perry?

374
00:26:04.897 --> 00:26:07.765
It's Mason. Perry
is my first name.

375
00:26:09.034 --> 00:26:10.093
I have a son.

376
00:26:12.004 --> 00:26:13.302
What's his name?

377
00:26:16.608 --> 00:26:17.735
Theodore.

378
00:26:17.843 --> 00:26:18.867
Teddy.

379
00:26:20.913 --> 00:26:22.404
How old?

380
00:26:22.481 --> 00:26:24.040
Nine in February.

381
00:26:28.220 --> 00:26:29.449
Charlie likes turtles.

382
00:26:32.091 --> 00:26:33.184
Liked.

383
00:26:37.396 --> 00:26:38.864
What's your boy fond of?

384
00:26:43.068 --> 00:26:44.092
Firetrucks.

385
00:26:49.308 --> 00:26:50.571
I bet.

386
00:26:52.277 --> 00:26:55.145
Nine is a good age for a boy.

387
00:27:07.493 --> 00:27:08.654
So...

388
00:27:11.296 --> 00:27:12.491
I'm sorry.

389
00:27:22.608 --> 00:27:23.985
Yeah. fine. he's a hothead.

390
00:27:24.009 --> 00:27:25.910
but he's a little too
touchy if you ask me.

391
00:27:26.678 --> 00:27:28.112
And her?

392
00:27:28.180 --> 00:27:30.911
She was just sitting
downstairs the whole time?

393
00:27:30.983 --> 00:27:33.543
She told the detectives
she gave the boy a bath.

394
00:27:33.652 --> 00:27:34.847
put him to bed.

395
00:27:34.953 --> 00:27:38.117
fell asleep by the fire
listening to the radio.

396
00:27:38.190 --> 00:27:40.455
Actually. she puts
Charlie to bed.

397
00:27:40.526 --> 00:27:42.495
goes downstairs to
clean up the kitchen.

398
00:27:42.561 --> 00:27:44.462
goes back upstairs
to check on him

399
00:27:44.530 --> 00:27:46.362
then goes downstairs
and falls asleep

400
00:27:46.465 --> 00:27:47.694
listening to the radio.

401
00:27:48.834 --> 00:27:50.826
She doesn't twitch an eyelid

402
00:27:50.936 --> 00:27:54.668
while someone creeps into
her house and nabs her kid?

403
00:27:54.740 --> 00:27:57.505
- You think she's a drinker?
- No. She's a mother.

404
00:27:58.277 --> 00:28:01.008
Feeding. changing.
burping. screaming.

405
00:28:01.113 --> 00:28:02.479
you wouldn't last a minute.

406
00:28:02.548 --> 00:28:04.148
Is this something
you know about?

407
00:28:04.983 --> 00:28:06.815
Call it an educated guess.

408
00:28:11.690 --> 00:28:13.659
All right. You're the kidnapper.

409
00:28:13.725 --> 00:28:15.751
you have to case that
house long enough to know

410
00:28:15.861 --> 00:28:17.557
Matthew's hours
at the grocery store.

411
00:28:17.663 --> 00:28:19.894
the time Emily gives
Charlie the bath.

412
00:28:19.998 --> 00:28:20.998
then puts him down.

413
00:28:21.233 --> 00:28:22.599
then falls asleep herself.

414
00:28:22.701 --> 00:28:24.329
Unless you have
someone on the inside.

415
00:28:24.403 --> 00:28:26.565
Oh. so you agree
with the police.

416
00:28:26.672 --> 00:28:29.198
You think the Dodsons
had something to do with it.

417
00:28:29.308 --> 00:28:31.937
- I'm not agreeing with anyone.
- I sure hope not.

418
00:28:32.044 --> 00:28:33.239
I've stood with those two.

419
00:28:33.912 --> 00:28:36.313
That's grief. not guilt.

420
00:28:36.615 --> 00:28:38.243
I'm just pointing out
that someone knew

421
00:28:38.350 --> 00:28:40.148
they were good
for a hundred grand.

422
00:28:40.219 --> 00:28:41.710
How do you figure
that from a guy

423
00:28:41.787 --> 00:28:44.848
who sells pickled
cucumbers and aftershaves?

424
00:28:44.923 --> 00:28:46.414
It's queer from both sides.

425
00:28:46.525 --> 00:28:47.788
And the baby.

426
00:28:49.094 --> 00:28:52.496
Someone stood over Charlie
and stitched those eyes.

427
00:28:56.034 --> 00:28:57.696
Yeah. it's a dark tone.

428
00:28:57.769 --> 00:29:00.170
long. long. deep. dark tone.

429
00:29:03.976 --> 00:29:05.911
Wipe it off. gentles.

430
00:29:05.978 --> 00:29:07.606
We do what we're asked to do.

431
00:29:07.713 --> 00:29:10.046
Well. that's easy
for you to say.

432
00:29:10.115 --> 00:29:12.260
Detectives aren't gonna like
me over their shoulder on this.

433
00:29:12.284 --> 00:29:13.728
And I got a license
that could get pulled.

434
00:29:13.752 --> 00:29:15.029
So you don't want the job?

435
00:29:15.053 --> 00:29:17.079
Did I say that?

436
00:29:17.556 --> 00:29:20.355
Bring me a signature
and a check.

437
00:29:23.895 --> 00:29:24.954
Cheer up.

438
00:29:25.063 --> 00:29:27.259
Someone might
throw a shoe at you.

439
00:29:28.267 --> 00:29:30.634
And you. get your hands
off my liquor and yourself

440
00:29:30.736 --> 00:29:32.637
down to the Angel's
Flight in the morning.

441
00:29:32.738 --> 00:29:34.468
Be my eyes. son.

442
00:29:35.073 --> 00:29:36.371
Time and a half.

443
00:29:36.441 --> 00:29:38.410
- It's New Year's Eve.
- Earn it.

444
00:30:16.348 --> 00:30:17.839
Very good. <i>papi.</i>

445
00:30:22.688 --> 00:30:24.350
I think she's jealous of me.

446
00:30:29.861 --> 00:30:33.320
Did you bring some
more of that tequila?

447
00:30:33.432 --> 00:30:34.798
It's called mescal.

448
00:30:34.866 --> 00:30:36.858
And if you want some.
you better get it yourself.

449
00:30:36.968 --> 00:30:38.459
I ain't your fucking help.

450
00:30:47.546 --> 00:30:50.072
Either take them off or
put them back on. <i>papi.</i>

451
00:30:50.182 --> 00:30:51.343
Make up your mind.

452
00:30:51.450 --> 00:30:53.214
What are you in a rush for?

453
00:30:53.318 --> 00:30:55.913
- I need sleep.
- Sleep here.

454
00:30:56.021 --> 00:30:57.819
I sleep in my own bed.

455
00:31:01.159 --> 00:31:03.094
I'll give you 6.000
for this dump.

456
00:31:03.328 --> 00:31:06.389
Ha. ha! Six thousand and
she won't even sleep here.

457
00:31:07.199 --> 00:31:08.633
It's a fair price.

458
00:31:08.700 --> 00:31:10.100
It's a price.

459
00:31:10.202 --> 00:31:12.103
It's a great fucking price.

460
00:31:12.204 --> 00:31:13.832
You don't even have citrus.

461
00:31:13.905 --> 00:31:15.498
You know I'm working this one.

462
00:31:15.574 --> 00:31:16.872
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

463
00:31:22.013 --> 00:31:23.413
It's a big case.

464
00:31:23.515 --> 00:31:25.416
You don't usually do the bigs.

465
00:31:26.385 --> 00:31:27.580
I'm doing this one.

466
00:31:29.955 --> 00:31:32.481
Six thousand five hundred.

467
00:31:33.759 --> 00:31:35.421
Enjoy your bed.

468
00:31:35.527 --> 00:31:36.586
I will.

469
00:31:48.407 --> 00:31:51.104
<i>And right there. in
that very window.</i>

470
00:31:52.110 --> 00:31:54.102
sat the boy's parents.

471
00:31:54.212 --> 00:31:57.705
Watching. hoping.
tragically unaware...

472
00:31:57.783 --> 00:32:02.551
that their tiny innocent was
already ascending to heaven

473
00:32:02.621 --> 00:32:06.456
in the clutches of this demon.

474
00:32:06.558 --> 00:32:09.255
This instrument of death.

475
00:32:10.328 --> 00:32:12.422
Thank you. ma'am.
Happy New Year. sir.

476
00:32:12.531 --> 00:32:15.695
Happy New Year!
Horror at Angel's Flight.

477
00:32:15.767 --> 00:32:17.998
baby murdered.
read all about it.

478
00:33:43.154 --> 00:33:44.679
Looking for something?

479
00:33:45.557 --> 00:33:47.150
Close the blinds. Steve.

480
00:33:47.626 --> 00:33:50.562
Maybe I couldn't see him so
good and shot him by accident.

481
00:33:50.662 --> 00:33:54.099
Look. fellas. if
I... interrupted

482
00:33:54.199 --> 00:33:57.328
some sort of tender
moment. I sincerely apologize.

483
00:33:57.402 --> 00:33:58.495
Guy's a laugh riot.

484
00:33:58.570 --> 00:34:00.095
Take it easy with that thing.

485
00:34:00.839 --> 00:34:02.831
What the hell are you
doing here. Mason?

486
00:34:02.908 --> 00:34:04.519
You gotta know something
stinks around Dodson

487
00:34:04.543 --> 00:34:05.841
or else you wouldn't be here.

488
00:34:05.911 --> 00:34:07.855
Get paid to look into
things. That's what I'm doing.

489
00:34:07.879 --> 00:34:09.905
Hell with this. We
got him on a B&E.

490
00:34:10.015 --> 00:34:11.392
Let's run him in.
torch his license.

491
00:34:11.416 --> 00:34:13.385
- Get the fuck off me.
- Settle down.

492
00:34:13.451 --> 00:34:15.215
Ease up. God damn it.

493
00:34:19.925 --> 00:34:21.757
You got something
says Dodson's clean.

494
00:34:21.860 --> 00:34:23.886
you'll be doing him a
favor by letting us know.

495
00:34:26.097 --> 00:34:29.761
Tiny innocent was already
ascending to heaven.

496
00:34:32.203 --> 00:34:34.468
Right after the Dodsons
found little Charlie dead.

497
00:34:34.573 --> 00:34:36.183
a green phaeton goes
tearing up Hill Street.

498
00:34:36.207 --> 00:34:37.539
clipped the trolley.

499
00:34:37.609 --> 00:34:39.771
You think that's our kidnapper?

500
00:34:39.878 --> 00:34:41.608
Where did you get
this phaeton shit?

501
00:34:41.713 --> 00:34:43.477
Traffic cop working
the bottom of the flight.

502
00:34:43.582 --> 00:34:45.059
He didn't think
anything of it at the time

503
00:34:45.083 --> 00:34:46.278
because most cops are stupid.

504
00:34:48.386 --> 00:34:49.581
Go check it out.

505
00:35:01.633 --> 00:35:03.727
Your ape almost broke my camera.

506
00:35:03.802 --> 00:35:05.794
My ape would've broke your jaw.

507
00:35:05.904 --> 00:35:07.202
- Here.
- What's that?

508
00:35:07.272 --> 00:35:08.763
For the car thing.

509
00:35:08.873 --> 00:35:10.637
Save it for a
better sketch artist.

510
00:35:10.742 --> 00:35:12.768
Man in hat? That
sure narrows it down.

511
00:35:12.877 --> 00:35:15.904
What about the guy on the
phone or the one in the car?

512
00:35:15.981 --> 00:35:17.472
